Ueli Aebi (born [[1946|31.05.1946]] in [[Bern]]) is a [[Switzerland|Swiss]] structural biologist and co-founder <ref> [http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/22115996/ National Center for Biotechnology: Looking back at a quarter-century of research at the Maurice E. M<U+00FC>ller Institute for Structural Biology].</ref> of the [[Maurice E. M<U+00FC>ller]] Instiute for [[Structural biology|Structure Biology]] at the [[Biozentrum University of Basel|Biozentrum]], [[University of Basel]].

== Life ==

Ueli Aebi studied [[physics]], [[Mathematics|mathematics]] und [[molecular biology]] at the [[University of Bern]] and Basel from 1967 to 1974, graduating in 1977 in [[biophysics]] at the University of Basel. After establishing his academic career in the USA ([[University of California, Los Angeles]]; [[Johns Hopkins University School of Medicine]], [[Baltimore]]), in 1986 he returned to the Biozentrum as Professor of Structural Biology. He was co-founder of the Maurice E. M<U+00FC>ller Institute for Structural Biology and its Director from 1986 until reaching [[emeritus]] status in 2011 <ref> [http://www.jnanobiotechnology.com/about/edboard/userprofile/2664559281881850 Journal of Nanobiotechnology] </ref> <ref>[http://www.biozentrum.unibas.ch/symposium-aebi/ Symposium in Honor of Prof. Ueli Aebi]</ref>
.

== Work ==

Ueli Aebi is recognized as a pioneer in integrative structural biology as well as [[Mechanobiology|mechano]]- and [[nanobiology]]. His work focused on the elucidation of the structure, function and assembly of the [[Cytoskeleton|cyto]]- and [[nucleoskeleton]] and the [[nuclear pore complex]] (NPC), as well as the [[amyloid]] [[fibrils]] being a hallmark in [[Alzheimer<U+2019>s disease]]. He studied the architecture of diverse [[supramolecular assemblies]] using a combination of [[Light microscopy|light]], [[Electron microscope|electron]] and [[atomic force microscopy]], [[X-ray crystallography]] and [[protein engineering]]. Among others, Aebi determined the [[Biomolecular structure|3-dimensional structure]] of the NPC by [[cryo-electron tomography]]. His seminal work opened the door to [[nanomedicine]] and thereby led to the development of novel nano-devices for diagnosis, treatment and prevention of [[connective tissue diseases]].

== Awards & Honors ==

* 1993 Elected Member of the [[European Molecular Biology Organization]] EMBO 
* 1999 Elected Member of the [[Academia Europaea]] 
* 2007 Dr. honoris causa (h.c.) from the 1st Medical Faculty, [[Charles University]], Prague, Czech Republic <ref> [http://www.biozentrum.unibas.ch/news-events/news-details/article/charles-university-in-prague-awards-prof-ueli-aebi-an-honorary-doctorate/ Biozentrum University of Basel: Charles University in Prague awards Prof. Ueli Aebi an honorary doctorate] </ref>
* 2011 Carl Zeiss Lecture Award of the German Society for Cell Biology (DGZ) <ref> [http://www.biovalley.ch/nc/news/lb-detail/article/two-prestigious-awards-for-ueli-aebi.html Two prestigious awards for Ueli Aebi] </ref>
* 2011 Distinguished Scientist Award of the [[Microscopy Society of America]] (MSA) <ref> [http://www.biozentrum.unibas.ch/news-events/news-details/article/two-prestigious-awards-for-ueli-aebi/ Biozentrum University of Basel: Two prestigious awards for Ueli Aebi] </ref>

== Publications ==

* Isenberg, G., Aebi, U. and Pollard, T.D. (1980). An Actin-binding Protein from Acanthamoeba Regulates Actin Filament Polymerization and Interactions. ''Nature'' (Lond.) '''288''': 455-9. [[PubMed Identifier|PMID]] [http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/6893736 6893736] 

* Aebi, U., Fowler, W.E., Isenberg, G., Pollard, T.D. and Smith, P.R. (1981). Crystalline Actin Sheets: Their Structure and Polymorphism. ''J. Cell Biol.'' '''91''': 340-51. [[PubMed Identifier|PMID]] [http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/7309785 7309785]

* Aebi, U., Cohn, J., Buhle, E.L. and Gerace, L. (1986). The Nuclear Lamina Is a Meshwork of Intermediate-type Filaments.  Nature (Lond.) 323: 560-4. [[PubMed Identifier|PMID]] [http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/3762708 3762708]

* Eichner, R., Sun, T.-T. and Aebi, U. (1986). The Role of Keratin Subfamilies and Keratin Pairs in the Formation of Human Epidermal Intermediate Filaments. ''J. Cell Biol.'' '''102''': 1767- 77. [[PubMed Identifier|PMID]] [http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/2422179 2422179]

* Reichelt, R., Holzenburg, A., Buhle, Jr., E.L., Jarnik, M., Engel, A. and Aebi, U. (1990). Correlation Between Structure and Mass Distribution of the Nuclear Pore Complex, and of Distinct Pore Complex Components. ''J. Cell Biol.'' '''110''': 883-94. [[PubMed Identifier|PMID]] [http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/2324201 2324201]

* Meyer, R.K. and Aebi, U. (1990). Bundling of Actin Filaments by alpha-Actinin Depends on its Molecular Length. J. Cell Biol. 110: 2013-24.[[PubMed Identifier|PMID]]
* Jarnik, M. and Aebi, U. (1991). Towards a 3-D Model of the Nuclear Pore Complex. ''J. Struct. Biol''. '''107''': 291-308. [[PubMed Identifier|PMID]] [http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/2351691 2351691]

* Pant<U+00E9>, N., Bastos, R., McMorrow, I., Burke, B. and Aebi, U. (1994). Interactions and 3-D Localization of a Group of Nuclear Pore Complex Proteins. ''J. Cell Biol.'' '''126''': 603-17. [http://jcb.rupress.org/content/126/3/603.full.pdf JCB]

* Wu, X.-R., Lin, J.-H., Walz, T., H<U+00E4>ner, M., Yu, J., Aebi, U. and Sun, T.-T. (1994). Mammalian Uroplakins, a Group of Highly Conserved Urothelial Differentiation-Related Membrane Proteins. ''J. Biol. Chem''. '''269''': 13716-24. [[PubMed Identifier|PMID]] [http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/8175808 8175808]

* Herrmann, H., H<U+00E4>ner, M., Brettel, M., M<U+00FC>ller, S., Goldie, K.N., Fedtke, B., Lustig, A., Franke, W.W. and Aebi, U. (1996). Structure and Assembly Properties of the Intermediate Filament Protein Vimentin: The Role of its Head, Rod and Tail Domains. ''J. Mol. Biol.'' '''264''': 933-53. [[PubMed Identifier|PMID]] [http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/9000622 9000622]

* Pant<U+00E9>, N. and Aebi, U. (1996). Sequential Binding of Import Ligands to Distinct Nucleopore Regions During Their Nuclear Import. ''Science'' '''273''': 1729-32. [[PubMed Identifier|PMID]] [http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/8781239 8781239]

* Goldsbury, C.S., Kistler, J., Aebi, U. Arvinte, T. and Cooper, G.J.S. (1999). Watching Amyloid Fibrils Grow by Atomic Force Microscopy. ''J. Mol. Biol.'' '''285''': 33-9. [[PubMed Identifier|PMID]] [http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/9878384 9878384]

* Burkhard, P., Kammerer, R.A., Steinmetz, M.O., Bourenkov, G.P. and Aebi, U. (2000). The Coiled-coil Trigger Site of the Rod Domain of Cortexillin I Unveils a Distinct Network of Inter- and Intra-helical Salt Bridges. ''Structure'' '''8''': 223-30. [[PubMed Identifier|PMID]] [http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/10745004 10745004]

* Lutzmann, M., Kunze, R., Buerer, A., Aebi, U. and Hurt, E. (2002). Modular Self-Assembly of a Y-Shaped Multiprotein Complex Made from Seven Nucleoporins. ''EMBO J.'' '''21''': 387-97. [[PubMed Identifier|PMID]] [http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/11823431 11823431]

* Strelkov, S.V., Herrmann, H., Geisler, N., Wedig, T., Zimbelmann, R., Aebi, U. and Burkhard, P. (2002). Evolutionarily Conserved <U+03B1>-Helical Segments 1A and 2B of the Intermediate Filament Dimer: Their Atomic Structures and Role in Filament Assembly. ''EMBO J.'' '''21''': 1255-66. [[PubMed Identifier|PMID]] [http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/11889032 11889032]

* Stoffler, D., Feja, B., Fahrenkrog, B., Walz, J., Typke, D., Baumeister, W. and Aebi, U. (2003). Cryo-Electron Tomography Reveals Novel Insights into Nuclear Pore Architecture - Implications for Nucleocytoplasmic Transport. ''J. Mol. Biol.'' '''328''': 119-30. [[PubMed Identifier|PMID]] [http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/12684002 12684002]

* Stolz, M., Raiteri, R., Daniels, A.U., Baschong, W. and Aebi, U. (2004). Dynamic Elastic Modulus of Articular Cartilage Determined at Two Different Levels of Tissue Organization by Indentation-Type Atomic Force Microscopy. ''Biophys. J''. '''86''': 3269-83. [[PubMed Identifier|PMID]] [http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/15111440 15111440]

* Lim, R.Y.M., Fahrenkrog, B., Koeser, J., Schwarz-Herion, K., Deng, J. and Aebi, U. (2007). Nanomechanical Basis of Selective Gating by the Nuclear Pore Complex. ''Science'' '''318''': 640-3. [[PubMed Identifier|PMID]] [http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/17916694 17916694]

* Stolz, M., Gottardi, R., Raiteri, R., Miot, S., Martin, I., Imer, R., Staufer, U., Raducanu, A., D<U+00FC>ggelin, M., Baschong, W., Daniels, A.U., Friederich, N.F., Aszodi, A. and Aebi, U. (2009). Early Detection of Osteoarthritis and Articular Cartilage Aging in Mice and Patient Biopsies by AFM. ''Nature Nanotechnology'' '''4''': 186-92. [[PubMed Identifier|PMID]] [http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/19265849 19265849]

* Plodinec, M., Loparic, M., Obermann, E.C., Zanetti-Dallenbach, R., Oertle, P., Hyotyla, J.T., Aebi, U., Bentires-Ali, M., Lim, R.Y.H. and Schoenenberger, C.-A. (2012). The Nanomechanical Signature of Breast Cancer. ''Nature Nanotechnology'' '''7''': 757-65 (see also: ''Nature'' '''491''' (''Nature Outlook'' 22-Nov-2012, S75-S83).  [[PubMed Identifier|PMID]] [http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/23085644 23085644]



